### Test Form Submission API
### You can use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code

### 1. Health Check (Test if API is running)
GET http://localhost:3000

###

### 2. Submit Form with JSON (No file uploads)
POST http://localhost:3000/form/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "interests": ["Website Development", "AI Powered System"],
  "budget": "$10,000 - $25,000",
  "message": "I'm interested in building a custom web application with AI features. Looking forward to discussing the project.",
  "newsletterSubscribed": true,
  "privacyPolicyAccepted": true
}

###

### 3. Submit Form with Multiple Interests
POST http://localhost:3000/form/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "interests": ["Blockchain Solutions", "Mobile App Development", "Cybersecurity Solution"],
  "budget": "$25,000 - $50,000",
  "message": "Need a secure mobile app with blockchain integration.",
  "newsletterSubscribed": false,
  "privacyPolicyAccepted": true
}

###

### 4. Submit Form without Message (Optional field)
POST http://localhost:3000/form/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Bob",
  "lastName": "Johnson",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "interests": ["MVP Development"],
